reviews.text: A new shopping mall above MTR Nam Cheong Station, cinema and restaurants inside, not very crowded

shops are ok and lots of restaurants here, all the parkings here have electric charger, also there are a bike racks for cyclists storing bikes free of charge too, with the MTR underneath, it is very convenient shopping mall
於7月26日開業，位於南昌地鐵站上蓋之新鴻基商場，除地下近深旺道有少量商舖外，大部份商舖位於L2層，共計130間舖，分佈於300,000平方呎之商場，內有超市(Fusion)，戲院(嘉禾院綫)，Uniqlo，Levi's，化妝品及食肆不計其數；此外，她有－天橋直達富昌薈，對住在匯璽之業主/租客，都甚為方便。
有戲院、食肆，首次舉加菲貓夏祭
區內新商場，店舖多，但一字長蛇陣鋪頭，一般好行。

A big station with quite a lot of stores after entering the gate. There are toilets in the station but beware of the AB and CD exit are far away and make sure you know which way to go before you leave the station. There is a lift to the ground level near the Exit A.

Nice MTR station same as other MTR stations in Hong Kong. Nicely managed crowd system for peak hours. Very helpful staff. Quick access to exits. Easy and fast access using octopus cards. Good facility for wheel chair and strollers. Thanks to MTR staff and management for making the journey healthy and quick.
Easy interconnections to the linked stations
One of the biggest MTR interchange stations that is famous for malfunctioned male washrooms.  Passengers, stop giving ourselves hard times.  The big Corp won't care your leak.
Good MTR station
車站附近交通購物都方便 轉乘鐵路亦相當快速
